Nairobi, Kenya: A man described by police as notorious for raiding M-Pesa shops was shot dead in a botched robbery in Kamukunji, Nairobi. According to the police, the suspect, in the company of three accomplices, had tried to rob an M-Pesa shop when an alarm was raised. His accomplices managed to escape on foot. During the shooting incident, police said a dog was killed by a stray bullet. Nairobi police boss Japheth Koome said the man was wanted for at least six robberies on M-Pesa shops in the area. ALSO READ: It&rsquo;s our mandate to police Pesalink, says CA boss